167
00:13:02.476 --> 00:13:04.892
How do you see your character, Iván?

168
00:13:07.601 --> 00:13:12.059
I've thought a lot about Pedro
all these months.


169
00:13:13.393 --> 00:13:15.392
I think Pedro's...

170
00:13:16.518 --> 00:13:20.100
driving force has been
to outdo his younger brother


171
00:13:20.268 --> 00:13:21.600
in front of their parents.
*


172
00:13:21.893 --> 00:13:25.350
So let's say that Pedro
has done everything right,


173
00:13:25.518 --> 00:13:30.100
he's always been steadfast,
secure, even with women.


174
00:13:30.935 --> 00:13:32.392
A football fan,

175
00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:37.100
a touch of the macho,
aggression, nationalism...


176
00:13:37.268 --> 00:13:39.642
He channels the primitive side,

177
00:13:39.810 --> 00:13:43.975
joining other primates
on the bleachers of the stadium.


178
00:13:44.768 --> 00:13:46.517
He gets up early.

179
00:13:47.185 --> 00:13:51.100
He's a simple, optimistic man.

180
00:13:51.268 --> 00:13:54.642
And I think that
he never wanted children,


181
00:13:54.810 --> 00:13:57.392
although he ended up
with one at this late stage.


182
00:13:57.560 --> 00:14:02.184
I love the idea of two brothers
forming a single entity,


183
00:14:02.351 --> 00:14:04.600
but split into two bodies.

184
00:14:04.810 --> 00:14:06.309
Look.

185
00:14:06.810 --> 00:14:09.767
They try to lead their lives
on different paths,


186
00:14:09.935 --> 00:14:12.934
but an unexpected event
puts them in opposition.


187
00:14:13.101 --> 00:14:13.684
Yes, yes.

188
00:14:13.851 --> 00:14:17.517
The fate of one is irrevocably linked
to that of the other.


189
00:14:17.685 --> 00:14:19.434
In fact, what happens to one,

190
00:14:19.601 --> 00:14:22.100
-happens to the other, right?
-Exactly.


191
00:14:23.685 --> 00:14:26.309
Félix, how do you see your character?

192
00:14:28.935 --> 00:14:32.559
Manuel, my character, doesn't exist.

193
00:14:33.018 --> 00:14:35.809
Pedro, his character, doesn't either.

194
00:14:35.976 --> 00:14:36.684
-Oh no?
-No.


195
00:14:36.976 --> 00:14:39.100
They're black ink on white paper.

196
00:14:39.518 --> 00:14:44.017
I don't need to know my character's past,
because he doesn't have one.


197
00:14:44.268 --> 00:14:48.684
I'll study the words and say them
with conviction and authority.


198
00:14:48.893 --> 00:14:52.225
That'll be enough,
the people will see Manuel.


199
